  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I retrieve deleted messages on messenger?",
  "response": "Retrieving deleted messages on Facebook Messenger can be challenging because once a message is deleted, it is typically removed from both the sender's and recipient's chat history. However, there are a few methods you can try to recover deleted messages:\n\n### 1. **Check the \"Archived Chats\" Folder**\n   - If you archived the chat instead of deleting it, the messages might still be accessible.\n   - Open Messenger, tap on your profile picture, and select \"Archived Chats\" to see if the conversation is there.\n\n### 2. **Use the \"Download Your Information\" Tool**\n   - Facebook allows users to download a copy of their data, which might include deleted messages.\n   - Go to **Facebook Settings > Your Facebook Information > Download Your Information**.\n   - Select the data range and include \"Messages\" in the categories.\n   - Download the data and check the HTML or JSON file for the deleted messages.\n\n### 3. **Check Email Notifications**\n   - If you have email notifications enabled for Messenger, you might find snippets of the deleted messages in your email inbox.\n\n### 4. **Ask the Other Person**\n   - If the message was deleted only from your side, the other person might still have a copy. Politely ask them to check their chat history.\n\n### 5. **Third-Party Recovery Apps (Use with Caution)**\n   - Some third-party apps claim to recover deleted messages, but be cautious as they may compromise your privacy or security. Always research thoroughly before using such tools.\n\n### 6. **Check on Another Device**\n   - If you\u2019ve used Messenger on another device, the messages might still be stored locally on that device.\n\n### 7. **Contact Facebook Support**\n   - In rare cases, you can contact Facebook Support and explain the situation. However, Facebook generally does not provide deleted messages due to privacy policies.\n\n### Important Notes:\n   - If a message was unsent using the \"Remove for Everyone\" feature, it is permanently deleted and cannot be recovered.\n   - Always back up your important conversations to prevent accidental loss in the future.\n\nIf none of these methods work, it\u2019s likely that the messages are permanently deleted and cannot be retrieved.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
